  }
  animation {
    rating: "Great"
    comments: "The movie is visually stunning and shows why Miyazaki and Ghibli are key influences for bringing eastern animation to the western world"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is pretty good for the most part, slows down a bit towards the end"
  climax: "Climax is the best as it feels kinda forced to be feel-good, an issue I have with a lot of Ghibli movies"
  tone: "Tone is very similiar to other Ghibli movies"
  final_notes: "Watched English Dub"
  overall: "Overall, a pretty good movie that uses stunning Ghibli animation to create an allegory about the US invasion of Iraq, but the movie is held back by its ending being too safe and feel-good"
